Step-by-Step Instructions:
Step 1: Access Gitea UI
Click on the "Gitea UI" button located on the top bar of your environment

Step 2: Login to Gitea
Username: jon

Password: Jon_pass123

Click "Sign In"

Step 3: Locate the Repository
Once logged in, you'll see the dashboard

Use the search bar at the top or browse to find the repository named sarah/story-blog

You can also navigate directly if you see it in the repository list

Step 4: Fork the Repository
Click on the sarah/story-blog repository to open it

Look for the "Fork" button (usually located in the top-right corner of the repository page)

Click the "Fork" button

Step 5: Configure Fork Settings
A fork configuration page will appear

Ensure the owner is set to jon (your user)

You can keep the same repository name or modify it if needed (but keep it as story-blog unless specified otherwise)

Click the "Fork" button to confirm

Step 6: Verify the Fork
After forking, you should be redirected to your forked repository

The URL should show: jon/story-blog

Verify that you can see all the files and commit history from the original repository

